UI Actions (ServiceNow)
🔹 What are UI Actions?

UI Actions in ServiceNow are used to create interactive buttons, links, and context menu options that allow users to perform actions directly from forms or lists.

They combine UI elements + server/client-side logic to execute operations.

🔹 Features
Create custom buttons and links
Execute scripts on click
Perform server-side or client-side actions
Available on forms and lists
Improves user productivity
🔹 Types of UI Actions
1. Form Button

Displays as a clickable button on a form.

Example:
Submit, Resolve, Close Incident

2. Form Link

Displays as a clickable text link.

Example:
View Related Records

3. List Choice

Appears in list context menu or actions.

Example:
Update Selected Records

4. Context Menu Action

Displays in right-click menus.

Example:
Export Records

🔹 Components
Name → UI Action name
Table → Table where action appears
Condition → Determines visibility
Script → Executes action logic
Action Name → Internal identifier
🔹 Example

Scenario: Create a button to close an incident.

Condition:

current.state != Closed

Action:

current.state = 'Closed';
current.update();
action.setRedirectURL(current);
🔹 Benefits
Simplifies record actions
Reduces manual steps
Supports automation
Enhances user interaction
🔹 Client vs Server UI Actions
Client UI Action	Server UI Action
Runs in browser	Runs on server
Immediate UI updates	Updates database
Uses client scripts	Uses server scripts
